Trying a new social media experiment of “giving” instead of asking for things on here-for me, it’s easy to treat these apps as a way to farm revenue or attention, and I’ve been asking myself what it would be like to just start giving and making instead of asking or advertising for things as much. So here’s a first little piece, a song I wrote recently plus my morning coffee/beach situation. Hope you have a good day today:)

Train rides on toor + a song about manhood that I forgot about til that morning when I recorded it. Anyways, see you on toor:)

In the middle of the wildest tour of my life which is actually two tours at the same time. Have a few days off to record new music before heading out into the madness again, and am taking a second to reflect. I feel so thankful that this is my job and that I think we sound pretty good, and that you guys are interested at all. I miss my new home in San Diego, but I feel very loved by my road family, & hopefully we’ve provided some fun times & some inspiration for those of you that have come out. See you in Raleigh this weekend with Ben n the boys to kick off the last month of shred :) 📸 @samcstreet
